        <h2>Equal Height Columns</h2>
        <p>Equal height columns can be achieved by adding the <code>equalize</code> modifier class to a <code>row</code>. This uses Javascript to detect the tallest column within that row and apply that height to each additional column within it. NOTE: Semantic support for this feature is currently not available as the Javascript component relies on the class to trigger this functionality.</p>
